      "evidence_quote": "In \"The Borrowed Name,\" Jordan's decision to adopt a false screen name seems, at first, like a small act of self-protection.",
      "rationale": "Demonstrates little subject-specific knowledge for the assigned task (theme in Jason Reynolds' Ghost). The response discusses a different text and does not include Ghost-specific details (characters, events) or required MLA-style quotations from Reynolds."
    },
    {
      "criterion_id": "K2",
      "level": "3",
      "score": 75,
      "evidence_quote": "the author uses that choice to examine a larger tension: anonymity can create space to experiment, but it can also erode integrity",
      "rationale": "Shows considerable understanding of the central idea (anonymity vs. integrity) and explains the relationship between choices and identity, though this understanding is not anchored to the assigned novel."
    },
    {
      "criterion_id": "T1",
      "level": "4",
      "score": 85,
      "evidence_quote": "That line is revealing because it is less a belief than a strategy.",
